prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Small and medium scale sellers can list their products in the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "E-Retail is an online marketplace application case study where small and medium scale sellers can list, showcase, advertise and sell their products directly to the customers without any physical store."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Sellers can showcase their products in the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "E-Retail is an online marketplace application case study where small and medium scale sellers can list, showcase, advertise and sell their products directly to the customers without any physical store."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Sellers can advertise their products in the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "E-Retail is an online marketplace application case study where small and medium scale sellers can list, showcase, advertise and sell their products directly to the customers without any physical store."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Customers can view all the products available from various sellers in the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "Customers can view all the products available from various sellers and buy those products."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Customers can purchase products online through the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "It also facilitates online payments for purchasing the products."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Customers can rate or give a review for the product in the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "Customers can rate or give a review for the product and seller."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Customers can report a seller for any violations in delivery or if the product does not meet the specified requirement in the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "Customers can also report a seller for any violations in delivery or if the product does not meet the specified requirement."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Customers can view the contact information and rating of the seller before buying the product in the application.",
      "evidence_quote": "Customers can also view the contact information and the rating of the seller before buying the product (Figures 9.1–9.9)."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Sellers can easily authenticate and signup to the portal.",
      "evidence_quote": "New sellers can easily authenticate and signup to the portal and sell their products in the portal."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The application offers separate login for sellers and customers.",
      "evidence_quote": "The application offers separate login for sellers and customers, where the sellers and customers can sign in and start using the application."
    }
  ]
}

